    {
      "id": "1904750c-f3ba-804a-afae-e748b9102c61",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "One of the main bottlenecks to the deployment of KT approaches is the sparseness in exercise data. To circumvent this issue,. the authors propose that KT models could incorporate pre-requequisites into the KT model. Authors introduce pre-requisites in the form of a constraint and show, on 5 datasets, that this alteration improves the standard KT approaches.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1904750c-f3ba-804a-afae-e748b9102c61",
